### Student Life OS API Testing

### Register a new user
POST https://localhost:7000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

###

### Login with existing user
POST https://localhost:7000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@studentlifeos.com",
  "password": "TestPassword123!"
}

###

### Login with newly registered user
POST https://localhost:7000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123!"
}

###

### Test with invalid credentials
POST https://localhost:7000/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@studentlifeos.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### Test with invalid registration (duplicate email)
POST https://localhost:7000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another User",
  "email": "test@studentlifeos.com",
  "password": "AnotherPassword123!"
}

###

### Test with invalid registration (weak password)
POST https://localhost:7000/api/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Weak User",
  "email": "weak@example.com",
  "password": "123"
}
